Section Header: A. Stratified Recruitment Data
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, Nursing home resident | 2, Nursing home staff

Field Label:
Nursing Home Residents

Inclusion criteria:

  • Current resident (long-term or short-stay) of a participating NH facility.
  • Willing to complete study procedures including nasal swabbing (2 separate swabs once per day) for 14 days (28 swabs) if they test positive, and nasal swabbing (2 separate swabs once per day) every day for 7 days (14 swabs) if their roommate tests positive. If they test positive and agree to the sub-study, nasal swabbing (2 separate swabs twice weekly) for an additional 14 days (8 swabs) and then nasal swabbing (2 separate swabs once per week) for an additional 60 days (18 swabs). There will be up to two short surveys and a symptom check each time swabs are taken (up to 28 times).
  • Capable of providing informed consent by oneself or through a designated legal guardian.

Exclusion criteria:

  • Resident has impaired decision-making capacity and does not have a legal guardian.
  • Resident or legal guardian is unwilling to provide consent.
  • The individual has previously requested that they not be contacted regarding research studies.
  • Resident or legal guardian is unable to communicate in English.

Nursing Home Staff

Inclusion Criteria:

  • Currently employed or contracted on-site by NH facility.
  • Willing to complete study procedures.
  • Capable of providing informed consent.

Exclusion Criteria:

  • Unwilling to provide consent.
  • Unable to communicate in English.

Section Header: A. Stratified Recruitment Data

Nursing Home Residents

Inclusion criteria:

  • Current resident (long-term or short-stay) of a participating NH facility
  • Willing to complete study procedures including up to 2 swabs every day for 14 days (28 swabs) if they test positive, and up to 2 swabs every day for 7 days (14 swabs) if their roommate tests positive. If they test positive and agree to the sub-study, 2 swabs twice weekly for an additional 14 days (8 swabs) and then 2 swabs once per week for an additional 60 days (18 swabs). There will be up to two short surveys and a symptom check each time swabs are taken (up to 28 times)
  • Capable of providing informed consent by oneself or assent through a designated legal guardian

Exclusion criteria:

  • Resident has impaired decision-making capacity and does not have a legal guardian
  • Resident or legal guardian is unwilling to provide consent
  • The individual has previously requested that they not be contacted regarding research studies
  • Resident or legal guardian is unable to communicate in English

  3. Any time swabs are collected for the study, [c2_calctext_3] may be asked about illness symptoms.
  4. We will access [c2_calctext_4] medical records at the nursing home and may also ask [c2_calctext_3] to confirm specific demographic and health data, including COVID-19 history and vaccination status and whether [c2_calctext_10] been diagnosed with other conditions like heart disease, cancer, and HIV.
  5. Overall, if you agree to be in the first part of the study, [c2_calctext_3] may receive up to 28 additional nasal swabs for study purposes. We will pay you for providing these additional swabs.
  6. One of the tests we use tests for both COVID-19 and influenza. We will share any clinically relevant test results with you and the nursing home. We will also share results with the state health department as required.
  7. At the end of the 14-days, you will be asked if you want to continue participating in an extended part of study. If you agree to be in this extended study, [c2_calctext_3] will be asked to provide two nasal swabs twice per week for another 2 weeks and then every week for up to 3 months. [c2_calctext_6] may refuse to be tested any day, and our team will return to ask if [c2_calctext_8] feel like getting tested during that 90-day period. This sub-study will involve 26 swabs.

BENEFITS

There are some other things you should know about participating.

You will be paid for [c2_calctext_11] nasal swabs, answering survey questions, and allowing us to access [c2_calctext_4] health records. You will receive X dollars for the initial survey, X dollars for each day of swabbing, and an additional X dollars if [c2_calctext_3] complete at least three-quarters of the expected nasal swabs. There is no cost to you or your insurance for participating in this study. [c2_calctext_2] participation in this study also has a chance to teach us a lot about COVID-19, which could benefit [c2_calctext_3], or someone you know, in the future.

RISKS/DISCOMFORTS

A possible risk of participating in this additional testing is brief discomfort when collecting your nasal swabs or a very small risk of injury such as a nosebleed. There is also a small chance that someone could access your information without permission; we will take every precaution to stop this from happening. Information that could identify [c2_calctext_3], such as your name or email address, will be removed from the data for all data analysis.

Do you have any further questions about this study or need me to repeat any information? Do you want to think about it or talk to a family member before agreeing to be a part of the study?

Do you understand that if you consent to be in this study we will be asking you for additional nasal swabs that you may not need to get if you were not part of the study?

CONTACT INFORMATION

All of this information, including the incentive structure, instructions, risks and benefits, and confidentiality information, will be provided to you in writing.

If you have more questions about the study, you may speak to [contact] at [study_forms_arm_1][b2_site]. If you think [c2_calctext_3] have been harmed by [c2_calctext_4] participation in the study, please contact [contact] and mention that you are calling about the SARS-CoV-2 Shedding in Nursing Home Staff and Residents (INHERENT) Study. Good morning/afternoon/evening, 

My name is [user-fullname], and I am a member of the INHERENT study staff. The INHERENT study is a study about COVID-19 in nursing homes being conducted by the CDC, Abt Associates, and [study_forms_arm_1][b_site]. INHERENT staff are helping your nursing home staff conduct COVID-19 testing according to public health guidelines.

Someone in your unit or facility recently tested positive for COVID-19, so you are being tested as recommended by public health guidelines. INHERENT staff are helping your nursing home staff conduct this COVID-19 testing. We are asking you to provide two nasal swabs today and, if you test negative for COVID-19, we will provide testing for [# - depends on whether consented roommate or other individual] more days in the coming week. Your swabs will also be tested for influenza , the virus that causes the flu. 
 
We will provide your results to the nursing home. If needed, someone from your nursing home care team will follow up with you about  next steps.  
 
Do you have any questions before I take the swabs? Is it OK if I collect the swabs now?
